<h2>Numeric Handler Demo</h2>

The <a name="numeric_demo">numeric handler demo</a> shows how to use the following numeric handler attributes:  <a href="#sum"> Sum</a>, <a href="#diff"> Difference</a>, <a href="#prod"> Product</a>, <a href="#quot"> Quotient</a>, <a href="#rem"> Remainder</a>, <a href="#sort"> Sort</a>.
<p>

<hr>
<a name="sum"><h3> Sum Numbers Separated by Whitespace </h3></a>
<b> Description:</b> Adds the numbers: 10 20 30 40 9.5, and returns the result.<br>
<br>
<b> Input:      </b>&lt;numeric sum&gt;10 20 30 40 9.5&lt;/numeric&gt;<br>
<br>

<b> Result:     </b><numeric sum>10 20 30 40 9.5</numeric>
<hr>

<h3> Sum an HTML Encoded List of Numbers </h3>
<b> Description:</b> Adds the numbers: 100 200 300<br>
<br>
<b> Input:</b>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;numeric sum&gt;&lt;li&gt;100 &lt;li&gt;200 &lt;li&gt;300&lt;/numeric&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;<br>
<br>

<b> Result:</b><ul><numeric sum><li>100 <li>200 <li>300</numeric></ul>
<hr>


<a name="diff"><h3> Using the Difference Attribute </h3></a>
<b> Description:</b> Compute the difference between 14 and 17.  This should return -3.<br>
<br>
<b> Input:</b>&lt;numeric difference&gt; 14 17 &lt;/numeric&gt;<br>
<br>
<b> Result: </b><numeric difference> 14 17 </numeric>
<hr>


<a name="prod"><h3> Using the Product Attribute </h3></a>

<b> Description:</b> Compute the product of 9 and 9.<br>
<br>
<b>Input:</b>&lt;numeric product&gt;9 9&lt;/numeric&gt;<br>
<br>
<b>Result:</b><numeric product>9 9</numeric>
<hr>

<a name="quot"><h3> Using the Quotient Attribute</h3></a>
<b> Description:</b> Compute the quotient of 20 and 10.<br>
<br>
<b>Input: </b>&lt;numeric quotient&gt;20 10&lt;/numeric&gt;<br>
<br>
<b>Result: </b><numeric quotient>20 10</numeric>
<hr>

<a name="rem"><h3> Using Remainder Attribute </h3></a>
<b> Description:</b> Compute the remainder of 17 and 10.<br>
<br>
<b>Input:</b>&lt;numeric remainder&gt;17 10&lt;/numeric&gt;<br>
<br>
<b>Result:</b><numeric remainder>17 10</numeric>
<hr>

<a name="sort"><h3> Sort a List of Numbers in Ascending Order</h3></a>

<b> Description:</b> Sort 88 77 11 99 in ascending order.<br>
<br>
<b>Input:</b>&lt;numeric sort&gt;88 77 11 99 &lt;/numeric&gt;<br>
<br>
<b>Result:</b><numeric sort>88 77 11 99 </numeric>
<hr>

<h3> Sort a List of Numbers in Descending Order </h3>

<b> Description:</b> Sort 88 77 11 99 in descending order.<br>
<br>
<b>Input:</b>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;numeric sort reverse&gt;&lt;li&gt;88&lt;li&gt;77&lt;li&gt;11&lt;li&gt;99&lt;/numeric&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;<br>
<br>
<b>Result:</b><ul><numeric sort reverse><li>88<li>77<li>11<li>99</numeric></ul>
